- ✅ Always handle errors with try/catch when using async/await to prevent unhandled rejections.
- ✅ Use Promise.all() for performing multiple asynchronous operations concurrently for better performance.
- ✅ Keep asynchronous functions small and focused for easier testing and debugging.
- ✅ Avoid nested async/await by using separate functions to maintain readability.

## Common Pitfalls
- ❌ Forgetting to return a Promise in an async function, which can lead to unexpected errors.
- ❌ Neglecting to handle errors properly, which can result in unhandled promise rejections.
- ❌ Overusing async/await for simple operations that can be handled with traditional callbacks or Promises.
- ❌ Causing performance issues by awaiting multiple Promises sequentially instead of concurrently.

